You can establish a data foundation in Marketing Cloud Engagement in multiple ways. Each customer implementation is unique and has different factors to consider.

This solution kit describes only how to use Data Cloud as the primary data foundation within Marketing Cloud Engagement.

Considerations
 DATA CLOUD MARKETING
CLOUD ENGAGEMENT DATA FOUNDATION	OTHER MARKETING CLOUD ENGAGEMENT DATA
FOUNDATIONS
Implementation Strategy Overview	
Use Data Cloud to activate core audiences to Marketing Cloud Engagement, and then connect the resulting data extensions to the Engagement Contact Model.
Core data extensions contain commonly used attributes that can be used for content personalization and decisioning across many different Journey Builder use cases.

Customer Traits and Considerations	

Your organization:

Wants to remove or minimize existing processes for importing data directly to Marketing Cloud Engagement
Is confidently able to import and harmonize required data within Data Cloud
Understands that the data foundation refreshes from Data Cloud to Marketing Cloud Engagement occur every 12+ hours

Implementation Pattern Overview	

Core Audience Model

Use Data Cloud to activate two core data extensions containing your full audience and all required attributes.

Collective Core Audience Model

Use Data Cloud to activate multiple core data extensions containing your full audience and all required attributes.

Synchronized Data Sources

Use Marketing Cloud Connect to establish a data foundation by syncing CRM contact and attribute data directly from Salesforce CRM and into the Engagement Contact Model.

External Systems

Use your own external systems or third-party tools to establish a data foundation.
